<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1847</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Senate so far has kept its agreement not to proceed with election of
                            President.* * * In all probability after Monday next Senate will proceed
                            and Dr. Henríquez will probably be elected.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>